<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-673-546  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 673 546.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DEC Professional  May 1990 v9 n5 p72(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Rdb/VMS: a tunable feast. (relational data bases)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mahler, Andy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>For optimal performance, relational databases need to bemonitored, making changes in their physical design for greaterefficiency.andP;  How the data is to be stored and accessed willdetermine how well the design works, and physical design of adatabase requires a knowledge of the system.andP;  Implement indexes inorder to achieve faster retrieval and to avoid sequential searchesthrough the database.andP;  Make sure page size is greater, but not toomuch greater, than the record size in order to avoid datafragmentation.andP;  Rdb/VMS provides utilities that offer a richtuning and monitoring environment.andP;  The RMU/DUMP utility indicatesthe size and placement of the database storage files.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Relational Data BasesUtility ProgramsPerformance ImprovementManagementData Base MaintenanceData Base Design.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>